, holotype aedeagus. Scale bars A &amp; B) = 0.5 mm; C &amp; D) = 100 μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B91FA72F712CA75BB8CFF41C25C78F5" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis id="B95A2660F712CA75BB8CFF41C3A97890" box="[199,252,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">Legs</emphasis>
: Moderately long, tarsal segments relatively narrow and elongate. Basal three tarsomeres with pad of suction setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B91FA72F712CA75BB8CFF09C22E79A9" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis id="B95A2660F712CA75BB8CFF09C26178D9" box="[199,308,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">Aedeagus</emphasis>
: Elongate (
<figureCitation id="1315E6F7F712CA75BAF1FF09C15B78D9" box="[442,526,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[165,1420,393,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-104@2.[152,1436,381,1908]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Protozantaena species. A) P. labrata Perkins, 1997, paratype, Namibia, Naukluft, habitus and labels; B) P. birdi sp. nov., holotype habitus; C) P. labrata, paratype, Namibia, Naukluft, aedeagus; D) P. birdi sp. nov., holotype aedeagus. Scale bars A &amp; B) = 0.5 mm; C &amp; D) = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6420503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6420503/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">Fig 1D</figureCitation>
), gonopore bearing flagellum very long, arcuate, bending toward base, as long as or longer than main-piece; supporting flagellum shorter. Main piece straight or nearly so in ventral view, with abrupt narrowing approx. 0.3 from apex; in lateral view arcuate, with distinct shift in angle of curvature just before mid-point of length and markedly narrowing in width towards setose area, where widened; parameres very short, each with two setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
